<br>
Dagnor's Cauldron: Invis and Endurebreath/DMF didn't see anything down there but never hurts to be careful<br>
<br>
Highpass hold: everything was green to me, no aggro. Shallow water. Just get a map it's confusing<br>
<br>
Oasis: Druid wolf form and invis. Get Enduring breath. They don't see through invis, and con apprehensive to wolf form.<br>
<br>
Lake Rathe: Druid wolf form and invis. Get Enduring breath. Goblins won't see through invis, deep won't either, wolf form is apprehensive. Wolf form is key because if invis drops, your screwed.<br>
<br>
Neriak: Make a Darkelf and plot your course through there. Neither the newbie guards nor inside guards see through invis. To be on the safe side, get Sow. I had a friend make a newbie Darkelf and nuke the guards so they chased him giving me free play in neriak.<br>
<br>
I have four more to do. Will post after I do them. So far I've been lucky. There was a raid of kledge getting togeather as I exited unrest with my first rod, so I got a DMF from one of the necros there. Rathe and Oasis there were druids able to cast wolf form within the zone. I keep several invis and endure breath potions on me, and so far it's been a breeze.<br>
<br>
Silvius Wayfarer<br>
35th Wizard of Drinal<br>
&quot;***Warning*** Prepare for Evac, Place your characters close, or kiss your xp goodbye&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilvius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/4/01 12:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PART II</span><hr size=1> Lower Guk: UGH! this is a cruel joke. I met a 41st wizard also doing the quest. First of all it took us about 20 min. to find our way to lower guk (never been there before) and then it took us another 45 minutes to bribe err hire a 55ish necro to invis v undead us, take us to the reanimated hand room, and kill the spawns. Cost us 100p, but no deaths. Once the spawns were dead, 2 or 3 min and we were gone with 2 rods. <br>
<br>
Erud's crossing: Easy. Didn't see any killer sharks at all. The plauge shark was flying through the air at the other side of the island. Enduring, invis, no sweat. (I endure for all of these, one less thing to worry about)<br>
<br>
Qeynos Catacombs: Go in invis from the Secret passage outside the NQeynos newbie area, just go along the right wall till you see a panel of stone with vines on it. Easy to get there. The Rod is bugged. It spawns, and despawns real quick. Took my 5 tries to get it. Sharks in pit don't see through invis.<br>
<br>
Everfrost: Endure, invis, swim north from hole. Keep right on the wall til you come to the house. Skels didn't agro until I got the rod. Might want to root or take them out first as I couldn't gate with them hiting me so I had to nuke them.<br>
<br>
Silvius Wayfarer<br>
35th Wizard of Drinal<br>
